Why do people believe fake news? How do you spot a fake story? How do politicians use misinformation to win votes? Find answers to these and other questions in our Election Check podcast series, published on citypress.co.za. Episode one covers zombie claims, confirmation bias and why people won’t let old lies die. In episode two, our experts share tips on sorting fact from fiction. Episode three takes a closer look at politicians’ role in the spread of misinformation. The fourth and last episode deals with fighting misinformation in WhatsApp groups.    